---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting - Lavelle Pty Ltd"
  description="Senior consulting services from Lavelle Pty Ltd: project recovery, PMO stand-up, business case development, procurement advisory, steering committee governance and delivery assurance."
  currentNav="consulting"
>
  <!-- SUB-PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="subhero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="subhero__crumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; <a href="/services">Services</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp;
        <span>Consulting</span>
      </div>
      <h1>
        Senior delivery expertise, when delivery is the <em
          >thing that matters most.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="subhero__lead">
        Lavelle Pty Ltd provides project recovery, PMO stand-up, business case
        development, procurement advisory, steering committee governance and
        delivery assurance to organisations running their most consequential
        change. Engagements are led personally by Sky Lavelle, with twenty years
        of complex program delivery across media, higher education and
        cybersecurity research - most recently leading two concurrent
        workstreams at a time under CIDO governance at the ABC.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__ctas" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">
          Request an engagement conversation <span class="btn__arrow">→</span>
        </a>
        <a href="#capabilities" class="btn btn--ghost"
          >See the six capabilities</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW WE WORK -->
  <section style="background:var(--paper);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <header class="section__head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">How we work</div>
          <h2 class="section__title" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
            Three operating <em>principles.</em>
          </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          Every engagement is different. The way we run them isn't. These three
          principles shape how Lavelle shows up - from the first conversation to
          the post-engagement handover.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="principles-grid">
        <div>
          <div
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); line-height:1; margin-bottom:1rem;"
          >
            01
          </div>
          <h3
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:1.55rem; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:0.75rem;"
          >
            Senior, by default.
          </h3>
          <p style="color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:var(--body-sm);">
            You get Sky on the engagement, not Sky on the proposal and a
            graduate on the work. Lavelle does not subcontract delivery to
            junior staff and we say no to engagements where that would be
            required.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); line-height:1; margin-bottom:1rem;"
          >
            02
          </div>
          <h3
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:1.55rem; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:0.75rem;"
          >
            Practical, never theatrical.
          </h3>
          <p style="color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:var(--body-sm);">
            Governance only counts when it changes behaviour. We design
            artefacts and cadence that the executive will actually use - not the
            prettiest version of a framework anyone could buy off the shelf.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); line-height:1; margin-bottom:1rem;"
          >
            03
          </div>
          <h3
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:1.55rem; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:0.75rem;"
          >
            Handover beats hand-holding.
          </h3>
          <p style="color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:var(--body-sm);">
            Every engagement has a defined endpoint. We build the artefacts,
            train the team, leave the playbook and step out. The success metric
            is whether your people can run the program without us six months
            later.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE SIX CAPABILITIES -->
  <section id="capabilities">
    <div class="wrap">
      <header class="section__head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">The six capabilities</div>
          <h2 class="section__title" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
            From diagnosis<br />to <em>handover.</em>
          </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          Six closely related services. Most engagements draw on two or three.
          Read each in detail - or jump straight to the one matching the problem
          you're holding.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="split">
        <div class="prose">
          <!-- 01 RECOVERY -->
          <article
            id="recovery"
            style="padding-bottom:3rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom:3rem;"
          >
            <div class="eyebrow">01 · Recovery</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              The Lavelle Recovery Protocol&trade;
            </h2>
            <p>
              When a program is red - or about to be - the first sixty days
              decide whether it can be recovered or needs to be reset. The
              Recovery Protocol&trade; is a four-phase methodology that runs
              from the day Lavelle is engaged to the day permanent delivery
              leadership takes back the wheel. Every artefact, every meeting
              and every escalation maps to one of the four phases.
            </p>

            <h3>The four phases</h3>
            <ol class="recovery-phases">
              <li>
                <div class="recovery-phase__head">
                  <span class="recovery-phase__num">Phase 1</span>
                  <span class="recovery-phase__days">Days 1-10</span>
                </div>
                <h4>Diagnose</h4>
                <p>
                  Independent diagnostic across scope, schedule, governance,
                  capability and stakeholder alignment. Output: the 30-day
                  Note - a written, board-ready statement of where the program
                  is and what recovery requires.
                </p>
                <p class="recovery-phase__artefacts">
                  <strong>Artefacts:</strong> Project Assurance Checklist,
                  RAID Register, Sponsor Update One-Page.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <div class="recovery-phase__head">
                  <span class="recovery-phase__num">Phase 2</span>
                  <span class="recovery-phase__days">Days 11-25</span>
                </div>
                <h4>Re-baseline</h4>
                <p>
                  Re-cut scope, schedule and budget with traceable rationale.
                  Output: the Re-baseline Pack - Stage Plan, revised Cost Plan
                  and an Exception Plan that the steering committee can sign
                  off without rewriting.
                </p>
                <p class="recovery-phase__artefacts">
                  <strong>Artefacts:</strong> Stage Plan, Cost Plan, Project
                  Change Request, Exception Plan.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <div class="recovery-phase__head">
                  <span class="recovery-phase__num">Phase 3</span>
                  <span class="recovery-phase__days">Days 26-40</span>
                </div>
                <h4>Re-govern</h4>
                <p>
                  Reset the governance pattern around the recovered baseline.
                  Output: the Re-governance Pack - SteerCo Charter rewrite,
                  Highlight Report cadence, RAG calibration and a decision
                  rights map that names who decides what.
                </p>
                <p class="recovery-phase__artefacts">
                  <strong>Artefacts:</strong> SteerCo Charter, Highlight
                  Report, Report Specification, RAG Rating Guide.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <div class="recovery-phase__head">
                  <span class="recovery-phase__num">Phase 4</span>
                  <span class="recovery-phase__days">Days 41-60</span>
                </div>
                <h4>Re-mobilise</h4>
                <p>
                  Hand the recovered program back to permanent delivery
                  leadership with the artefacts in place and the operating
                  cadence running. Output: the Recovery Closure Note - a
                  written handover that names what was fixed, what is still
                  fragile and what the next steering committee needs to watch.
                </p>
                <p class="recovery-phase__artefacts">
                  <strong>Artefacts:</strong> Recovery Closure Note, End
                  Project Report (partial), Operational Acceptance Criteria.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>

            <h3>The recovery ladder</h3>
            <p>
              Recovery is not one product. It is a ladder of engagement
              intensities, all built on the same Protocol&trade;. Pick the
              rung that matches the size of the program and the budget for
              recovery work.
            </p>
            <div class="recovery-ladder">
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>Project Recovery Checklist</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Free · self-serve</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">Free</div>
                <a href="/free-tools/project-recovery-checklist"
                  >Download&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>Project Recovery Pack</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Artefact set · self-serve</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$1,247</div>
                <a href="/templates/project-recovery-pack">View pack&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>Project Recovery Bundle</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Framing doc + four artefacts</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$2,997</div>
                <a href="/bundles/project-recovery-bundle">View bundle&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row recovery-ladder__row--anchor">
                <div>
                  <strong>Recovery Diagnostic Report</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">5-day independent diagnostic</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$13,500</div>
                <a href="/contact?subject=recovery-diagnostic">Book&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>30-Day Recovery Sprint</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Phases 1-2 embedded</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$58,000</div>
                <a href="/contact?subject=recovery-sprint">Enquire&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>60-Day Recovery Engagement</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Phases 1-4 embedded</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$99,000</div>
                <a href="/contact?subject=recovery-engagement">Enquire&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
              <div class="recovery-ladder__row">
                <div>
                  <strong>90-Day Recovery + Hypercare</strong>
                  <span class="recovery-ladder__sub">Phases 1-4 plus 30-day hypercare</span>
                </div>
                <div class="recovery-ladder__price">$144,000</div>
                <a href="/contact?subject=recovery-hypercare">Enquire&nbsp;→</a>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Recoverable vs unrecoverable</h3>
            <p>
              Not every program is worth recovering. Part of an honest
              Diagnostic Report is naming when the right call is reset rather
              than recover. Lavelle will tell you, in writing, when the
              evidence points to reset - and what a credible reset path looks
              like.
            </p>
            <div class="recovery-filter">
              <div>
                <div class="eyebrow">Recoverable when</div>
                <ul>
                  <li>The business case still holds with a re-baselined scope</li>
                  <li>The sponsor is willing to back a reset to the steerco</li>
                  <li>The delivery team has the capability to execute the recovered plan</li>
                  <li>The vendor and contractual position is repairable</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="eyebrow">Reset is the right call when</div>
                <ul>
                  <li>The business case no longer survives honest re-evaluation</li>
                  <li>Sponsor support has eroded past the point of recovery</li>
                  <li>The capability gap is too large to close inside the recovery window</li>
                  <li>Contractual position is irreparable and no exit clause is exercisable</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="recovery-cta">
              <p>
                If your program is in trouble, the highest-conversion next
                step is a Recovery Diagnostic Report. Five days, written
                output, single price - book the call and we will scope it on
                the spot.
              </p>
              <a
                href="/contact?subject=recovery-diagnostic"
                class="btn btn--primary"
              >
                Book a Recovery Diagnostic Report
                <span class="btn__arrow">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- 02 PMO -->
          <article
            id="governance"
            style="padding-bottom:3rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom:3rem;"
          >
            <div class="eyebrow">02 · Governance</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              PMO stand-up &amp; uplift
            </h2>
            <p>
              The PMO is the operating system of complex delivery. Done well,
              it's the calm machinery that lets senior leaders focus on the few
              decisions that matter. Done badly, it's a status-report factory
              that nobody reads. Lavelle stands up new PMOs and uplifts existing
              ones - designing the artefact set, cadence and reporting line that
              matches your delivery complexity rather than imposing a generic
              framework.
            </p>
            <h3>How we help</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                PMO operating model design (charter, mandate, escalation
                pathway)
              </li>
              <li>
                Artefact library: status, RAID, decision logs, change control,
                benefits
              </li>
              <li>
                Cadence design: weekly, monthly and quarterly rhythms that
                actually fit
              </li>
              <li>
                Tooling configuration (Jira, Smartsheet, Microsoft 365 stack,
                ServiceNow)
              </li>
              <li>PMO team uplift and capability development</li>
              <li>Independent PMO health check, where one already exists</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Typical engagement</h3>
            <p>
              Eight to twelve weeks for a stand-up. Four to six weeks for a
              targeted uplift or health check.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- 03 BUSINESS CASE -->
          <article
            id="investment"
            style="padding-bottom:3rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom:3rem;"
          >
            <div class="eyebrow">03 · Investment</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              Business case development
            </h2>
            <p>
              Treasury-grade and ICT business cases that survive scrutiny. We
              write the case the executive will need to defend in front of the
              budget committee - not the one the template asked for. Strong
              benefits logic. Honest assumptions. Risk articulated in language a
              non-technical board can interrogate.
            </p>
            <h3>How we help</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Strategic, outline and full business case authorship for
                executive delegate approval
              </li>
              <li>Benefits realisation logic and measurement plan</li>
              <li>Problem statement and initiative objectives framing</li>
              <li>Options analysis with credible counterfactuals</li>
              <li>Cost modelling and sensitivity analysis</li>
              <li>Risk register tied to mitigation accountability</li>
              <li>Executive narrative and decision-paper drafting</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Typical engagement</h3>
            <p>
              Six to twelve weeks depending on stage gate and supporting
              evidence base.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- 04 PROCUREMENT -->
          <article
            id="sourcing"
            style="padding-bottom:3rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom:3rem;"
          >
            <div class="eyebrow">04 · Sourcing</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              Procurement &amp; RFP advisory
            </h2>
            <p>
              The procurement event is where most delivery is won or lost - long
              before a single line of code is written. Lavelle helps you procure
              the right outcome by designing RFPs that actually test for
              capability, running evaluations that can withstand probity
              scrutiny and managing the handover from contract signature to
              operational delivery without the usual six-week gap.
            </p>
            <h3>How we help</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                RFP and EOI design - requirements, evaluation criteria, response
                structure
              </li>
              <li>
                Restricted RFP design for capability-critical procurements
              </li>
              <li>
                Probity-compliant evaluation governance, including large
                multi-function panels (e.g. 15-person panel across technical,
                finance, commercial and information security)
              </li>
              <li>
                Weighted evaluation methodology design (e.g. 70:30
                technical-to-financial)
              </li>
              <li>
                Vendor due diligence, BAFO, contract negotiation and delegate
                approval
              </li>
              <li>Vendor onboarding and delivery kickoff</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Typical engagement</h3>
            <p>
              Ten to sixteen weeks across pre-market, evaluation and
              contracting.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- 05 STEERING -->
          <article
            id="assurance"
            style="padding-bottom:3rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); margin-bottom:3rem;"
          >
            <div class="eyebrow">05 · Assurance</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              Steering committee governance
            </h2>
            <p>
              Most steering committees spend forty minutes hearing what already
              happened and ten minutes deciding what to do next. That ratio is
              the wrong way around. Lavelle redesigns the steering pack, agenda
              and decision papers, so executive time is spent on the few
              decisions only they can make - and surfaces the issues that need
              surfacing before they become headlines.
            </p>
            <h3>How we help</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Steering committee charter, membership and decision rights
              </li>
              <li>Pre-read protocol and decision-paper structure</li>
              <li>Status dashboard design - RAG that means something</li>
              <li>Issue and risk escalation thresholds</li>
              <li>
                Independent steerco chair facilitation (where appropriate)
              </li>
              <li>
                Board reporting derived from, not duplicated by, the steerco
              </li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Typical engagement</h3>
            <p>
              Four to six weeks to design and embed. Often combined with a PMO
              uplift.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- 06 ASSURANCE -->
          <article id="independence" style="padding-bottom:3rem;">
            <div class="eyebrow">06 · Independence</div>
            <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1rem 0;">
              Delivery assurance
            </h2>
            <p>
              An independent senior pair of eyes on your most consequential
              delivery - before the board asks for one. Lavelle runs health
              checks, gate reviews and red-team analyses for programs where the
              cost of a missed warning sign vastly outweighs the cost of an
              external opinion. Confidential. Written. Useful.
            </p>
            <h3>How we help</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Confidential delivery health checks (two to four weeks)</li>
              <li>Gate review preparation and independent gate assurance</li>
              <li>
                Red-team analysis of program plans, business cases and
                procurement strategy
              </li>
              <li>
                Pre-board reviews - what the board will ask, before they ask it
              </li>
              <li>Vendor performance assurance during delivery</li>
              <li>Post-implementation review and benefits validation</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Typical engagement</h3>
            <p>
              Two to six weeks. Often the start of a longer engagement, but
              never required to be.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>

